# implement here
image_folder = '/content/drive/MyDrive/hw4_photos/images/'
output_folder_squares = '/content/drive/MyDrive/hw4_photos/squares/'
output_folder_faces = '/content/drive/MyDrive/hw4_photos/faces/'


image_files = os.listdir(image_folder)
num_images = len(image_files)
num_faces = 0

for filename in image_files: ## terate over the images and find faces
    image_path = os.path.join(image_folder, filename)
    image = cv2.imread(image_path)
    image_copy = image.copy() 
    face_locations = face_recognition.face_locations(image) ## detect faces in the image
    
    if len(face_locations) > 0:
        for face_location in face_locations:
            top, right, bottom, left = face_location
            
            cv2.rectangle(image, (left, top), (right, bottom), (255, 0, 0), 2) ## draw the blue squeres around faces
            squares_filename = os.path.splitext(filename)[0] + '_squares.jpg'
            squares_path = os.path.join(output_folder_squares, squares_filename)
            cv2.imwrite(squares_path, image)
 
            face_image = image_copy[top:bottom, left:right] ## save the face from the original image
            face_filename = os.path.splitext(filename)[0] + f'_face{num_faces}.jpg'
            face_path = os.path.join(output_folder_faces, face_filename)
            cv2.imwrite(face_path, face_image)
            
            num_faces += 1 ## count num of faces detected 

print('Number of images in the dataset:', num_images)
print('Number of faces detected:', num_faces)

Number of images in the dataset: 200
Number of faces detected: 291

output_folder_features = '/content/drive/MyDrive/hw4_photos/features/'

features_list = []
filenames_list = []
num_faces_with_features = 0

for filename in os.listdir(output_folder_faces):
    face_path = os.path.join(output_folder_faces, filename)
    face_image = cv2.imread(face_path)
    face_features = face_recognition.face_encodings(face_image) ## extract features using recognition_face
    
    if len(face_features) > 0:
        for i, features in enumerate(face_features):
            if len(features) == 128: ## check size of the features vector
                features_list.append(features)
                filenames_list.append(f"{filename}")
                num_faces_with_features += len(face_features)
    else: ## if it isnt a face delete it from folder
        os.remove(face_path)

print('Number of faces with features:', num_faces_with_features)

Find best K:¶

In [3]:
# implement here
df = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/hw4_photos/features/features.csv')
filenames_df = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/hw4_photos/features/filenames.csv') 
features = df.values

k_values = range(2, 90) ## set the rage up to 90 to find ideal k
inertia_values = []
silhouette_scores = []

for k in k_values: 
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=k, n_init=10, random_state=42)
    kmeans.fit(features)
    inertia_values.append(kmeans.inertia_)
    silhouette_scores.append(silhouette_score(features, kmeans.labels_))
In [ ]:
## now lets plot
fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))

## inertia values by k values
ax1.plot(k_values, inertia_values, marker='.', alpha=0.5)
ax1.set_xlabel('Number of Clusters (K)')
ax1.set_ylabel('Inertia')
ax1.set_title('K-means Inertia vs. Number of Clusters')
ax1.grid(True)

## silhouette scores by k values
ax2.plot(k_values, silhouette_scores, marker='.', alpha=0.5)
ax2.set_xlabel('Number of Clusters (K)')
ax2.set_ylabel('Silhouette Score')
ax2.set_title('K-means Silhouette Score vs. Number of Clusters')
ax2.grid(True)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

## find K value that gives the best silhouette 
max_silhouette_index = np.argmax(silhouette_scores)
best_k = k_values[max_silhouette_index]

print("Best K value based on Silhouette Score:", best_k)

Best K value based on Silhouette Score: 52

k = 52 ## our selected k val
features = df.values

kmeans_52.fit(features)

output_folder = '/content/drive/MyDrive/hw4_photos/clusters/'
os.makedirs(output_folder, exist_ok=True)

for cluster in range(k):
    cluster_folder = os.path.join(output_folder, f'cluster_{cluster}')

for i, row in filenames_df.iterrows(): ## save each face in the matching cluster folder
    filename = row[0]
    image_path = os.path.join(image_folder, filename)
    cluster_label = kmeans_52.labels_[i]
    cluster_folder = os.path.join(output_folder, f'cluster_{cluster_label}')

In [5]:
tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, random_state=42)  ## dimension reduction using TSNE
tsne_results = tsne.fit_transform(features)
cluster_labels = kmeans_52.labels_

unique_labels = np.unique(cluster_labels)  ## get the labels of the original kmeans (with 128 fratures)
num_clusters = len(unique_labels)
colors = ['#%06x' % random.randint(0, 0xFFFFFF) for _ in range(num_clusters)] ## get 52 distinct colors

medoids = []
for cluster in np.unique(cluster_labels): ## find the medoid of each cluster
    cluster_points = tsne_results[cluster_labels == cluster]
    total_distances = []
    for i in range(len(cluster_points)):
        distances = np.sum((cluster_points - cluster_points[i]) ** 2, axis=1)
        total_distance = np.sum(distances)
        total_distances.append(total_distance)
    medoid_index = np.argmin(total_distances)
    medoid = cluster_points[medoid_index]
    medoids.append(medoid)

X = tsne_results

neighbors = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=4) ## compute nearest neighbors distances
neighbors.fit(X)
distances, _ = neighbors.kneighbors(X)
distances = np.sort(distances[:, -1])

max_distance_index = np.argmax(distances)

plt.plot(range(1, len(distances) + 1), distances, color = "lightblue") ## plot the elbow curve
plt.xlabel('Distance to the 4th nearest Neighbor')
plt.axhline(y=1.4, color='grey', linestyle='--') 
plt.ylabel('Distance')
plt.title('Elbow Curve')
plt.show()

Maximum distance: 3.9841297521414694
In [7]:
eps = 1.4 ## set params 
min_samples = 2

data = tsne_results  
dbscan = DBSCAN(eps=eps, min_samples=min_samples)
clusters = dbscan.fit_predict(data)

unique_clusters = np.unique(clusters[clusters != -1])
num_clusters = len(unique_clusters) 
num_noise_points = np.sum(clusters == -1)

distinct_colors = ['#%06x' % random.randint(0, 0xFFFFFF) for _ in range(num_clusters)]
In [ ]:
## now lets plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
for i in range(len(tsne_results)):
    if clusters[i] == -1:
        marker = 'X'  ## mark noise points as X
        plt.scatter(tsne_results[i, 0], tsne_results[i, 1], color='black', alpha=0.8, marker=marker)
    else:
        marker = 'o'  ## mark data point in her cluster
        cluster_label = clusters[i]
        color = distinct_colors[np.where(unique_clusters == cluster_label)[0][0]]
        plt.scatter(tsne_results[i, 0], tsne_results[i, 1], color=color, alpha=0.5, marker=marker)

plt.title('DBSCAN Clustering on Two-Dimensional Data')
plt.xlabel('t-SNE Dimension 1')
plt.ylabel('t-SNE Dimension 2')
plt.show()

# implement here
df = pd.read_csv('/content/drive/MyDrive/hw4_photos/features/features.csv')
features = df.values

kmeans_52 = KMeans(n_clusters=52, n_init=10, random_state=42)
kmeans_52.fit(features)

tsne = TSNE(n_components=2, random_state=42)  ## dimension reduction using TSNE
tsne_results = tsne.fit_transform(features)

kmeans_tnse = KMeans(n_clusters=52, n_init=10, random_state=42)
kmeans_tnse.fit(tsne_results) ## predorm kmeans after the TNSE

dbscan = DBSCAN(eps=1.4, min_samples=2)
dbscan.fit(tsne_results)
